BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 17) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (And Gritch? Gritch became the most generous animal in the meadow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (He'd learned the hard way what greed does   it rots your treasure, kills what feeds you,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (and drives everyone away.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (Now he was always the first to help others find the ripest fruit, the first to share his) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (acorns in winter, the first to welcome new animals to the meadow.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td ('Aren't you afraid of running out?' a young squirrel once asked him.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td ('No,' Gritch smiled. 'I learned something important: sharing never makes less. It always) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td (makes more.') Tj ET
