BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 22) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (So here's what the Sharing Tree teaches us:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (When you share   your toys, your snacks, your time, your kindness   it doesn't leave you) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (with less.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (It actually gives you MORE: more friends, more happiness, more love coming back to you.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (But when you hoard and keep everything for yourself, it spoils. Like Gritch's fruit. It) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (rots when it's not shared.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (Be generous. Share freely. And watch your world grow into a beautiful grove of goodness.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.4 Td ([Illustration: A child sharing toys with friends, snacks with siblings, time with someone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td (lonely   showing that sharing in real life creates abundance and joy, warm and inviting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (final image]) Tj ET
endstream
